    <statement><p>The moment generating function for a discrete random variable is given by <m>M_X(t) = 0.7e^{3t} + 0.3e^{6t}.</m> For which value is <m>M_X(t)</m> equal to 3.9?  Give your answer to at least three decimal places.</p>
<p>Solution: <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>0.32143</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We can make a substitution <m>z = e^{3t}\text{.}</m>  Then, we have <m>{0.7z + 0.3z^2 = 3.9}\text{.}</m>  We can re-write this as <m>{0.3z^2 + 0.7z - 3.9 = 0.}</m></p>
<p>We can use the quadratic formula:</p>
<p><me>z = \frac{-0.7 \pm \sqrt{0.49 + 4.68}}{0.6} \approx -4.95627, 2.62294.</me></p>
<p>Recall that <m>z=e^{3t}\text{.}</m>  So, <m>e^{3t} = -4.95627</m> or <m>e^{3t} = 2.62294.</m> The first equation has no solution. Solving the second equation gives <m>t \approx 0.32143\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
